<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSES TO BOTH DOCS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Apr 26 23:51:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Yo, Doc Spatz,<br>
     More than one of us pointed to the continuing existence of Chinatowns and Little Italys, some over 100 years old, and enclaves like Amish farming communities, and you're going to beat the Vietnamese of Little Saigon over the head for not assimilating by your standards after a mere 20 years? The Know Nothings compained the same of the Irish in the 1840s and '50s. Give me a break. Also I'd check your demographics, and the last congressional election with Dornan losing. Orange county ain't so white bread anymore, but is getting a decided Hispanic flavor in many places.<br><br>
     Also if the Israelis are sick and tired of being held to a higher standard; I suggest they quit using the Torah as their primary claim document to the land being claimed for rule and being confiscated from Palestininians for housing developments. You can't have it both ways. Consider the passage in Numbers that begins: &quot;Remember when you were guests in the Land of Egypt...&quot;, and then goes on to cover proper treatment of non-Jews in the land. The Orthodox, especially, honor that in the breach. And that's not to call the Palestinians angels. Neither side has yet to really fully acknowledge the other side's rights. And how many American lives will be lost through terrorism and/or military action before a true peace ever comes?<br><br>
Both Docs,<br>
     I like to follow a good argument as well as anyone, but seeing you both verbally beat each other up is getting a bit painful to watch.  You're both screaming past each other. If either is upset about something the other said, FINE, but even a couple months on the internet doesn't give a person total insight to another's heart and motives. Take issue with an action, but please be more careful in assuming you know what someone's motivation is. I've always hated it when someone impugns someone else's basic principles with little or no knowledge, except for some screwups.         
